Secret coves, interesting fellow guests
Oct 2015 ‚Ä¢ Couples
Everything was great about the cruise apart from the weather. We had 3 days of almost no sun, but at least we didn‚Äôt have any rain and we missed the nearby typhoon ‚Äì and so our photos are not so great. But it‚Äôs still a very beautiful area. The staff were very helpful and organised, and the drivers from and back to Hanoi were steady and safe, which is quite an achievement considering the crazy traffic. The company had been very good in keeping in touch beforehand, and they phoned our hotel the night before to check that we had arrived and knew about pick-up arrangements. The bed was very comfortable and the meals great. We didn‚Äôt enjoy the ‚ÄòEuropean evening meal‚Äô as much (because it was too ‚Äònormal‚Äô for us, though no doubt special for the Taiwanese group who had joined us), but we enjoyed the Vietnamese cooking and spring roll cooking lesson. The main highlight of the trip was kayaking through sea caves into secret coves, which were totally tranquil. The other highlight was chatting to interesting, well-travelled fellow passengers. There were only about a dozen of us on our 2-night cruise, so we got to know each other quite well by the end. How to attract friendly, interesting guests on your cruises and avoid demanding, complaining folk? I don‚Äôt know‚Ä¶ Perhaps emphasise the ‚Äòadventure‚Äô part more than the luxury‚Ä¶? The wifi was intermittent, but this meant that sometimes we had to socialise instead of being glued to our iPhones, tablets and laptops.
