Doug K
Spokane, WA4,526 contributions
Well worth it, but do 2-nite tour
Oct 2015
Amazing plce, even if we didn't have perfect weather. Absolutely pay the extra in time and money for the 3-day tour. Day one you don't leave harbour until 1 pm, then cruise 1+ hour to the amazing cave. Nice if you like caves but you have paid for it in the tour already. Then back to boat and off to titop. 437 steps to view point (more than 40-story bldg) so be prepared as it is stepp and steps narrow in places. Or, just hang on the beach and wait for others to come down from view and join you in the water. Water very warm and nice. Dinner, maybe karaoke (they love it here). Kayak next morning, then back to harbour if one night trip. 2-night is more relaxed with kayak and beach next day and time to just read, lay on deck. Food on my trip was wonderful, seafood, many veggies and a little meat. Great presentation. 3-rd day is kayak in morning, then head back to harbour. Book at least 3 star boat, mine was 4-star (orienal seas)
